        <div id="content">
            <p><a href="http://adf.ly/">Adfly</a> is an annoying, broken, and virus-ridden url shortener that displays ads for 5 seconds before redirecting to the link's destination. To bypass it, simply send a request to <code>http://thesupremenerd.com/adf[.]ly/{adfly path}</code>.</p>
<pre><code>$ curl -i thesupremenerd.com/adfly/5XR
HTTP/1.1 302 Found
Content-type: text/plain
Location: http://www.google.com
Content-Length: 21
Date: Tue, 04 Dec 2012 20:54:59 GMT
Server: lighttpd/1.4.31

http://www.google.com
</code></pre>
<p>Example (goes to Google, derived from <a href="http://adf.ly/5XR">http://adf.ly/5XR</a>): <a href="http://thesupremenerd.com/adfly/5XR">http://thesupremenerd.com/adfly/5XR</a></p>
<p>The Python bypassing code can be found <a href="https://gist.github.com/4208956">here</a> under the MIT license.</p>
